Opponents of abortion argue that the measures serve to protect women’s health, although some also welcomed the effects of the closure of clinics.
Only one doctor who performs abortions in Louisiana has patient insemination rights, the Center for Reproductive Rights said.
If all other doctors in the state were forced to stop performing abortions, this doctor would no longer perform the operation out of fear for his safety, the group said.
In their argument against the ruling, Louisiana state officials said they would not punish doctors for performing abortions while their applications for patient access rights were still pending.
